cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC

This paper discusses a security system for IoT applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on access control for high-level programming languages, which suggests a potential fit for software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The use of system call interposition and memory domains indicates a potential fit for systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the performance overhead of the proposed system, which suggests a potential fit for distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category.
